            <title><![CDATA[Marvel Cosmic Invasion, A Retro 2D Beat-Em-Up, Coming Holiday 2025]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/marvel-cosmic-invasion-a-retro-2d-beat-em-up-coming-holiday-2025/1100-6530428/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/marvel-cosmic-invasion-a-retro-2d-beat-em-up-coming-holiday-2025.1146438/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/marvel-cosmic-invasion-a-retro-2d-beat-em-up-coming-holiday-2025/1100-6530428/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6530428">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Dotemu has revealed Marvel Cosmic Invasion, a retro 2D beat-em-up game featuring Marvel superheroes in a classic art style. Revealed during the <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/nintendo-direct-march-2025-all-the-biggest-announcements/2900-6377/" data-ref-id="2900-6377">Nintendo Direct</a>, Marvel Cosmic Invasion features up to four player co-op and has several Marvel characters you can play as to smack down alien invaders.</p><p>For each level you pick two characters, swapping between the two via team-up attacks, creating special combo attacks depending on which characters you choose. While only a handful of characters were shown in the reveal trailer, the <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2753970/MARVEL_Cosmic_Invasion/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Marvel Cosmic Invasion Steam page</a> states that there will be 15 playable characters to choose from.</p><p data-embed-type="video" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=19_uUhZsjsg" data-width="100%" data-height="100%">          <iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/19_uUhZsjsg" height="100%" width="100%" scrolling="no" frameborder="" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></p><p>The trailer revealed a handful of Marvel characters you can play as, like Wolverine, Captain America, Spider-Man, Venom, Nova, Phyla-Vell, and Storm. There was also a boss fight against Task Master shown, along with a brief glimpse of the Sentinel enemies from X-Men in the cinematic.</p><p>The big villain in Marvel Cosmic Invasion is Annihilus, and the game will take place across both earth and the larger galaxy as you battle against bug-like aliens and iconic Marvel villains. There are dynamic team-up attacks and you can play up to four player co-op both locally and online.</p><p>Marvel Cosmic Invasion is set to release in 2025 on Nintendo Switch, PlayStation 4, PlayStation 5, Xbox, and PC.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
